Being a potato would likely involve a simple, stationary existence. You'd spend your early life developing underground, surrounded by soil, without sight or sound as we understand them. Perhaps you'd experience the world through basic sensations like moisture, temperature, and the chemical composition of your surroundings. There would be no thoughts or worries—just a gradual growing process following your genetic programming until harvest time. It's a peaceful existence in many ways, though quite different from the complex consciousness and sensory experiences humans enjoy.

